strings.Value: "It's not my concern. I've already had enough trouble because of this story."
"Does this situation somehow threaten me or my kingdom?"
"Fine. We'll meet with these elves if circumstances permit."
"I'm not going to meddle in your affairs with the elves. This is my final decision."

"I bring news," {n}Jaethal reports abruptly.{/n} "Not unexpected. A sizable group of elves from {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g} has crossed the border into your kingdom. They send {g|JaethalQ3}a message{/g} to you. You may read it, if you wish, but I can state the substance in a few words: "We demand you turn over the murderer. We await your response."

{n}Jaethal stares at you closely, as if trying to assess something. Is she studying you, or considering the larger situation?{/n} "I... suppose we should meet with them. Back then, near the {g|Thorn River}Thorn River{/g}, after the battle with the elven youngsters, I felt {g|Urgathoa}Urgathoa's{/g} presence again — for the first time since I was reborn. Now I feel something similar. A command. Or the shadow of one. Besides, I don't like to leave my affairs unfinished. Let us put an end to this."
"Is there a chance I might change your mind? I can't see any reason for you to say no. This mission is extremely important to me. We'll both win if we resolve the situation — one way or another."
"I am ready to strike out at a moment's notice."

"I doubt it. They are not official emissaries from {g|Kyonin}Kyonin{/g}. — If they were, then their interference would look quite different. Most likely these are the families of those foolish youngsters from the camp near the {g|Thorn River}Thorn River{/g}. I assume they're inclined to fight, but they won't set ambushes or try to stab you in the back. First, they will surely try to negotiate. Elves, you know..." {n}Jaethal allows herself a sarcastic smirk.{/n}
"As you wish… I don't dare to distract Your Highness any further."
